09374nam a22012255i 9783839429570DE-B159720220629043637.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220629t20162016gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2019666833  a(OCoLC)954930367  a97838394295707 a10.1515/97838394295702doi  a(DE-B1597)453021  a(OCoLC)945035029  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE00aHQ1062 7aSOC0130002bisacsh00aAgeing and Technology :bPerspectives from the Social Sciences /ced. by Linda Nierling, Emma Domínguez-Rué.  a1. Aufl. 1aBielefeld : btranscript Verlag, c[2016] 4c©2016  a1 online resource (342 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aScience Studies00tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tAll that Glitters is not Silver - Technologies for the Elderly in Context. Introduction -- tAgeing, Technology and (Inter-)Personal Development: Old Agers as Technology Users -- tMotives of the Elderly for the Use of Technology in their Daily Lives -- tAn Exploration of Mobile Telephony Non-use among Older People -- tOlder Women on the Game: Understanding Digital Game Perspectives from an Ageing Cohort -- tSocial Inclusion of Elderly People in Rural Areas by Social and Technological Mechanisms -- tAgeing, Technology and Elderly Care: Assistive Technologies -- tSkripting Age - The Negotiation of Age and Aging in Ambient Assisted Living -- tMaking Space for Ageing: Embedding Social and Psychological Needs of Older People into Smart Home Technology -- tSeeing Again. Dementia, Personhood and Technology -- tEnabling a Mobile and Independent Way of Life for People with Dementia - Needsoriented Technology Development -- tEmotional Robotics in the Care of Older People: A Comparison of Research Findings of PARO- and PLEO-Interventions in Care Homes from Australia, Germany and the UK -- tPolicy making and Discourses of Ageing Policy making and Discourses of Ageing -- tNavigating the European Landscape of Ageing and ICT: Policy, Governance, and the Role of Ethics -- tAgeing and Technology Decision-making: A Framework for Assessing Uncertainty -- tAging and Technology: What is the Take Home Message for Newspapers Readers -- tTowards an Ageless Society: Assessing a Transhumanist Programme -- tFocusing on the Human: Interdisciplinary Reflections on Ageing and Technology -- tList of Authors0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aThe booming increase of the senior population has become a social phenomenon and a challenge to our societies, and technological advances have undoubtedly contributed to improve the lives of elderly citizens in numerous aspects. In current debates on technology, however, the »human factor« is often largely ignored. The ageing individual is rather seen as a malfunctioning machine whose deficiencies must be diagnosed or as a set of limitations to be overcome by means of technological devices.This volume aims at focusing on the perspective of human beings deriving from the development and use of technology: this change of perspective - taking the human being and not technology first - may help us to become more sensitive to the ambivalences involved in the interaction between humans and technology, as well as to adapt technologies to the people that created the need for its existence, thus contributing to improve the quality of life of senior citizens.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2017: Backlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSocial sciences (General). 0aTechnology and older people. 4aAging Studies. 4aBody. 4aSocial Sciences. 4aSociology of Technology. 4